Package org.palladiosimulator.analyzer.slingshot.annotations

Annotation Type ExtensionPoint

  • @Retention(SOURCE)
@Target(TYPE)
@Documented
public @interface ExtensionPoint
    This annotates the interface or class that is needed for an extension to either be extended from (in case of a class) or implemented (in case of an interface). Furthermore, this will generate a .exsd file under the schema directory that registers the extension point in the plugin.xml file.
    Author:
    Julijan Katic

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Fields Description
      static java.lang.String DEFAULT_IMPLEMENTATION_NODE
      The default value used in #xmlImplementationNode().

    • Required Element Summary

    • Field Detail

      • DEFAULT_IMPLEMENTATION_NODE

        static final java.lang.String DEFAULT_IMPLEMENTATION_NODE
        The default value used in #xmlImplementationNode().

    • Element Detail

      • id

        java.lang.String id
        This should give the id of the extension point. This will be used when creating the schema (.exsd) file and refering it in the plugin.xml. Also, this will be used in the extensions when refering to the extension point. This id should be unique within the Eclipse application.
        Returns:
        The id of this extension.

      • name

        java.lang.String name
        Returns a short name of the extension point. This is important for documentation.
        Returns:
        the name of the extension.

      • pluginName

        java.lang.String pluginName
        Returns:
        The non-null, non-empty name of the plugin in which the extension point lies.

      • providerNode

        java.lang.String providerNode
        Defines the corresponding node in the .exsd file that will contain the information (path) of the implementing class.
        Default:
        "client"
